        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Heber Springs, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dam Site Marina...                Hickory Flat...
Clay...                           Wilburn...
Providence...                     Crosby...
Searcy...                         Dewey...
Heber Springs...                  Center Hill...
Sidon...                          Pangburn...
Letona...                         Pickens in White County...
Armstrong Springs...              Sunnydale...
Albion...                         Velvet Ridge...
Steprock...                       Plainview in White County...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
